      "id": "bug-005",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-07T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "POST /api/computer-games/:id/move -> 500 Internal server error. Prisma: Unique constraint failed on the fields: (gameId, ply) at tx.move.create (computer-games.service.ts:252)",
      "file": "apps/api/src/computer-games/computer-games.service.ts",
      "root_cause": "When the side-to-moves clock has flagged, engine applyMove() (game-state.ts isTimeout early-return) returns the game as completed WITHOUT appending the attempted move. submitMove ignored this: it took state.moves[last] (the PREVIOUS move) and re-inserted it, duplicating its ply -> unique (gameId,ply) violation -> 500. Triggered whenever a computer game sat idle past its time control.",
      "fix": "In submitMove, after applyMove, guard: if state.moves.length === engineState.moves.length (no move appended = flag fall), persist game as completed with state.result/resultReason (timeout) and return WITHOUT creating a Move row. Verified: flagged game now returns 200 status=completed result=white_wins resultReason=timeout, no dup row; normal moves ply1-3 still 200.",
      "tags": [
        "computer-games",
        "timeout",
