      "id": "bug-007",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-07T00:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Playing vs Stockfish, idle a few mins, return shows game already lost but no checkmate",
      "file": "apps/api/src/computer-games/computer-games.service.ts, apps/web/src/components/play/computer-game-setup.tsx",
      "root_cause": "Computer games were created with a finite server clock (timeControlSeconds from the setup time-control picker). Engine applyMove -> isTimeout flags on real wall-clock elapsed since last move (nowMs - lastTickAt), so idling between moves drained the human clock and the next submit returned status=completed reason=timeout. But the in-game UI hardcodes clock \"∞\" / Time \"Unlimited\" and shows no countdown, so the timeout loss was an unexplained surprise (no checkmate).",
      "fix": "Made vs-computer games untimed to match the UI. submitMove now resets engineState.clock.lastTickAt = nowMs before applyMove, so isTimeout sees ~0 elapsed and never fires regardless of idle time. Removed the time-control picker from computer-game-setup.tsx; it now sends fixed UNTIMED_SECONDS=600/inc=0 only to satisfy the DTO/category column. Kept the existing flag-fall guard as a defensive dead path (bug-005 mock test still passes). typecheck clean (api+web), 16/16 service spec green.",
